This chunk contains three methods (`reset()`, `addMenuItem()`, and `popupSliders()`) that define core functionality within the Pmw-based vector entry classes for resetting values, adding menu commands, and displaying slider controls.

def reset(self):
        self.set(self['resetValue'])

    def addMenuItem(self, label = '', command = None):
        self.menu.add_command(label = label, command = command)

    def popupSliders(self):
        self._floaters.set(self.get()[:])
        self._floaters.show()
